The paper proposes a new regularization method for classifiers that focuses on the topological complexity of the classification boundary. This is a topic that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures (cs.DS). However, given that the paper is primarily focused on machine learning and classification, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.CV and cs.NE.
